data.name: _txtSearchName.ToolTip
data.value:
Name EA Model Search or *.sql file to quickly find your most interesting stuff: - Insert EA Model Search Name or *.sql file - If blank the default from configuration is used - Douple Mouse Click starts the Search - Enter starts the Search
Note: If you enter a SQL file name like 'Branch.sql' make sure the SQL Path is appropriate: - SQL Query Addin Tab - File, Settings

data.name: _btnConveyedItemConnector.ToolTip
data.value:
Get connectors with Conveyed Items from selected Element.
1. Select Element 2. Click Button CI Connector (Conveyed Item Connector) 3. EA outputs Search with Source Element of connector 4. Right Click, Find in Diagram 5. EA Shows all Diagrams where the Source Element 6. Explore the diagrams
There is no interface to directly access the connector (as far as I'm aware of)

data.name: _btnConveyedItemElement.ToolTip
data.value:
Get Conveyed Elements from selected Connector
1. Select Connector 2. Click Button CI Element (Conveyed Elements) 3. EA outputs Search with Elements 4. Right Click, Find in Project Browser
There is no interface to directly select more than one Browser Element (as far as I'm aware off)
